<br>
If the point was to see if the other raid is engaging, turn on invis, track one of their clerics, stand in the middle of their camp, and watch the spell messages and who is leaving to pull.<br>
<br>
If yer sooooo curious that you absolutely have to see the dragon, use tracking, stay at a distance, and if you are aggroed get a /loc and die.<br>
<br>
If RoS had a more than adequate force as claimed they did not need to retrieve the corpse of a 60 ranjur. If they had an adequate force as claimed and were ready, the ranjur would have been pulling and not checking on the other raid's state of readiness (by going to see the mob? Very strange).<br>
<br>
While wanting to CR is understandable, it does indicate a willingness to delay engaging the mob (CR, Res, buff, the ressed regains mana and returns to the mob). When every second counts, this seems unlikely. In the future ya might want to use Summon Coprse. It would be safer and perhaps even pose less risk of further delay. <br>
<br>
So which is it? A whole bunch of bad choices indicating a real lack of skill or finding a pretty slimy method to insure victory?<br>
